<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Carbon credits at risk of link to Uyghur forced labour bought by BP and Spotify]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/nov/13/carbon-credits-at-risk-of-link-to-uyghur-forced-labour-bought-by-bp-and-spotify]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T12:00:25Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4f1f1ccad38a8b8598a2895b0c8718c4966325ed/0_0_3000_1800 /master/3000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=67146a9c9c963acb10e9ad465a5d63f2&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;维吾尔族妇女在新疆田地里采摘棉花&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;BP 和 Spotify 等公司购买了该产品碳信用额有可能受到潜在影响&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/13/what-do-we-know-about-forced-labour-in-xinjian&quot; >;调查发现，维吾尔族强迫劳动。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这些信用额来自巴楚碳项目，该项目由世界上最大的碳咨询公司南极开发。该项目重点关注中国新疆的一座生物质发电厂，该发电厂表示，将通过利用附近田地的废棉秆发电来降低全球碳排放。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;South Pole 的首席执行官 Renat Heuberger，周五宣布退出，宣传其为妇女和少数民族提供就业福利以及支持联合国可持续发展目标的信用额度，这些说法经常得到购买它们以抵消碳足迹的公司的附和。在巴楚项目的广告资料中，该公司表示，该计划涉及“当地农民收集棉秆并燃烧以产生碳中和电力。这项活动既创造了可持续的电力，又为项目区的农村人口创造了额外的收入来源，从而促进了当地经济。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但是《卫报》和荷兰调查新闻编辑室 Follow the Money 分析了项目文件并指出核电站及其周边地区的卫星图像，查看了泄露的南极数据，并就中国政府对待维吾尔穆斯林的方式与几位专家进行了交谈。该团队发现了潜在的强制性劳动力转移，涉及项目 50 公里（30 英里）范围内两个地点的数百人，该项目在该半径内收集棉秆。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;c8de2591bf3de762b68d0500da44ba52dd3224ee &quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/c8de2591bf3de762b68d0500da44ba52dd3224ee/0_0_5472_3283/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;新疆哈密田地里等待运输的棉包&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;新疆哈密田地里等待运输的棉包。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Costfoto/NurPhoto/Shutterstock&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;调查发现，South Pole 意识到与 2021 年该计划相关的强迫劳动风险。South Pole 没有向购买积分的公司或认证机构 Gold Standard 提出担忧，卫报明白了。 South Pole 表示，在 2021 年提出尽职调查担忧后，该公司停止出售这些积分。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;《卫报》了解到，潜在客户和 South Pole 内部可能在 2021 年提出了强迫劳动可能与该项目有关的风险。 2021年，《卫报》看到的南极内部系统中，有一条说明称不向客户提供该计划的积分。它说“不要向 KAM 提供 – DD 问题”。 KAM代表大客户经理； DD 表示尽职调查。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;根据内部销售数据，South Pole 自 2014 年起就开始销售积分。对销售数据的分析显示，从中国合作伙伴那里购买的积分平均价格为 0.39 欧元，South Pole 以平均价格 4.28 欧元的价格出售给试图履行环境承诺的公司，产生了 657,529 欧元的销售额。该数据可能并不明确。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;根据数据，BP 从该项目中购买了最多的碳信用额，并将其作为 BP 目标中和计划 2020 年投资组合的一部分，该计划为人们提供了机会抵消驾驶造成的排放。英国石油公司拒绝置评，但仍将该项目列入其 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bp.com/en_gb/target-neutral/home/our-carbon-offset-project-portfolio/offset-projects-from- our-previous-portfolios.html&quot;>;发布时为 Target Neutral 网站&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;WWF、Spotify、网球运动员多米尼克·蒂姆 (Dominic Thiem)、Ecologi 和希尔顿酒店 (Hilton Hotels) 等都购买了积分根据黄金标准注册和南极销售数据，该项目。并非所有的作品都是由南极直接出售的。 WWF 和 Ecologi 分别于 2019 年和 2020 年停止支持该计划，他们告诉卫报。 Spotify、蒂姆和希尔顿酒店未回复问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;9181783d0767b717c86e26d0035a13245284885c&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/9181783d0767b717c86e26d0035a1324528488 5c/0_224_3365_2019/1000 .jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Spotify logo&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Spotify 是从该项目购买积分的公司之一。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Jakub Porzycki/ NurPhoto/Shutterstock&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;在一份回应调查结果的声明中，南极表示：“我们从未在实地拥有或管理过这个项目，因此我们有能力收集真实的信息时间和详细信息相对有限。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当客户对该项目潜在的劳工问题表示担忧时，我们对情况进行了具体审查。我们的审查未能发现任何值得关注的重大问题，但我们总体上对无关的媒体报道新疆强迫劳动的指控感到不安。因此，我们做出了谨慎的决定，在 2021 年停止销售该项目的碳信用额。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;金标表示赞赏“调查性新闻可能带来的审查”，并欢迎“有助于帮助解决问题的贡献”自愿碳市场改善并发挥其潜力，推动最重要的变革”。它证实南极在任何时候都没有向它提出过对巴楚的担忧。运营该发电厂的电力公司没有对问题作出回应。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;巴楚发电厂于 2008 年开始建设，位于中国西北部新疆喀什地区。它通过秸秆锅炉燃烧生物质（主要是周边地区的棉秆和木材）来发电，并输送到中国电网。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;近年来，世界各地都对新疆强迫维吾尔族劳工表示担忧。 。联合国&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ohchr.org/en/press-releases/2018/08/committee-elimination-racial-discrimination-reviews-report-china&quot;>;估计大约&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.chinafile.com/reporting-opinion/features/where-did-one-million-figure-detentions-xinjians-camps-come&quot;>;百万人&lt;/a>;被安置在自 2017 年以来，拘留营用来压迫维吾尔人和其他与汉族不同的少数民族。专家表示，强迫维吾尔人劳动和强迫土地转让很常见，通常与包括棉花行业在内的农业产业有关。&lt;/p>; &lt;旁白>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/jan/11/if-you-enter-a-camp-you-never- come-out-inside-chinas-war-on-islam&quot;>;“如果你进入一个营地，你就永远不会出来”：中国对伊斯兰教的战争内部&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;开源对工厂周围地区的卫星录像进行分析，发现同一地区有一个强化设施，研究人员已将其与该大规模设施联系起来。新疆维吾尔族穆斯林被拘留。没有证据表明该设施与棉花工业或巴楚生物质设施有关。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;《卫报》询问德国学者阿德里安·曾兹 (Adrian Zenz)，他是新疆棉花采摘行业强迫劳动问题最重要的专家之一。分析该地区的政府宣传和新闻报道。 Zenz 的工作一直是全球争论的话题，他发现了自 2011 年以来，有两个农场参与了该项目半径 50 公里范围内潜在的强制性劳动力转移的证据。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;其中一个农场曾在两份不同的当地新闻中被点名。有关劳动力转移的报道。第一份报告发生在 2016 年，描述了干部如何在一个村庄找到了 400 名能够采摘棉花的人，并将他们动员到包括相关农场在内的多个目的地。第二次是在 2018 年，有 930 人被重新安置到同一个农场。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;生物质设施 50 公里半径范围内的另一个农场在 2020 年的新闻报道中被指定为目的地，在本例中， 345名村民被组织去采摘棉花。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;出于安全考虑，无法独立核实实地报告，也无法确定这些农场是否提供了该植物。该电力公司没有回答我们关于其材料来源的问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;254e894bfcfba935cd58361f5a8def0fde533801&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/254e894bfcfba935cd58361f5a8def0fde533801 /0_194_5808_3485/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;新疆库车的棉田&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;新疆库车的棉田&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：VCG/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Zenz 表示，这些新闻报道已被专家广泛用作新疆强迫劳动的证据，表明该地区处于高风险之中。这一说法和新闻报道已经与其他专家就中国政府对待维吾尔族穆斯林的方式进行了核实。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“在新疆你找不到比这更危险的地方了。在世界上，你可能找不到比这个地方更危险的国家强制劳动的地方了，”他告诉卫报。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这是一个系统性的情况。事实上，我们在 50 公里半径内只有几个例子，有人可能会说：“哦，只有几个。”但我认为这就是我们在这里看到的症状……&lt;strong>; &lt;/strong>;通常情况下，国家强制劳工，不可能将特定批次的产品与特定的强制劳工动员联系起来。你不能这样做的原因是因为国家不提供或披露信息，你不能去那里审计。你不能问维吾尔人，因为如果他们不说正确的话，他们最终会被关进营地。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在回应有关潜在强迫劳动力转移的报道时，美国人类学家达伦·拜勒 (Darren Byler) 专门研究了这一问题。中国政府对待维吾尔人的方式表示：“总的来说，棉花和纺织是新疆使用指定或非自由劳动力的主要产业之一。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“没有办法抵抗，尤其是在这种情况下，在所谓的扶贫方面，对政府干预或管理的任何形式的抵制都是抵抗的迹象，并可能导致您被拘留。这些地区几乎每个人都认识被拘留的人，也许还有他们自己的家人。因此，这种威胁确实无处不在。”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;中国政府表示，劳动力转移计划是一种扶贫工具。新疆的贫困率高于中国其他地区。 2020年《政府白皮书》称，2017年至2019年，剩余劳动力计划喀什及附近的和田地区帮助13.5万人就业。白皮书显示，2014年至2019年，南疆地区平均每年通过富余劳动力转移安置168万人。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;2554cc113ba271f15fece918dd096495ba5a9729&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot; https://media.guim.co.uk/2554cc113ba271f15fece918dd096495ba5a9729/0_384_5757_3454/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;一名警察在宣传广告牌前打手势，敦促“维护新疆法治”&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;一名警察在宣传广告牌前打手势，敦促“维护新疆法治”。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Pedro Pardo/AFP/Getty Images &lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;中国驻伦敦使馆发言人表示，所谓新疆‘强迫劳动’是反华势力散布的谎言。这与新疆各族人民的劳动权益得到有效保障完全相反。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“中国各级政府充分尊重各族人民的意愿”组织就业工作，对报名参加相关工作岗位的人员进行必要的职业培训。新疆各族群众就业脱贫后脸上的笑容，就是对有关谎言和谣言最好、最有效的反驳。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;发言人补充说，郑国恩“以编造涉疆谣言、诽谤中国为生，没有任何信用和学术诚信。”他们指出，郑国恩目前正在被一些新疆企业和居民起诉，并强烈驳斥了他的分析。&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;“强迫劳动在新疆已经存在很长时间了”&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;据专家认为，劳动力转移计划通常涉及强迫劳动，特别是自 2017 年以来，以及因不遵守政府计划而被拘留在再教育营的威胁。中国政府文件指出，拒绝与劳动力转移计划等扶贫计划合作是极端主义的潜在迹象。这会使人面临被关进再教育机构的风险。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;专家表示，无法得知这些计划是否是自愿参与的，而且存在很高的胁迫风险。国际利益相关者很难对此过程进行独立的尽职调查。美国政府的立场是，除非能够证明事实并非如此，否则来自新疆的商品是通过强迫劳动生产的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;独立研究员 Nyrola Elimä 表示，棉花很可能“受到强迫劳动的污染” 。 “他们不能拒绝，因为他们有被送往拘留营、再教育营的风险。强迫劳动在新疆已经存在很长时间了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“维吾尔人很难说不。自2017年以来，你就不可能拒绝了，因为否则你就只能去再教育营。那么关于你在 2011 年与我分享的那篇文章，那肯定涉及强迫劳动。自 2011 年起，中国新闻和政府报告就讨论了涉及生物质设施周围村庄和农场数千人的劳动力转移计划。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;人们还担心碳信用额的环境完整性与该项目相关，因为尚不清楚该工厂的建设是否依赖碳收入。碳信用额要想有价值，就必须代表对气候的好处，而这种好处是无论如何都不会发生的。用于描述这一点的术语称为“额外性”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;宾夕法尼亚大学克莱曼能源政策中心高级研究员丹尼·卡伦沃德 (Danny Cullenward) 表示：“用于向该项目发放积分的方法不评估项目的额外性，这是假设的而不是分析的。这种遗漏在 20 世纪 90 年代可能是有道理的，但在今天，如果没有碳信用额收入，此类项目在商业上不可行的假设是不可信的。”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这些发现是在越来越严格的审查中得出的。南极作为碳项目开发商的角色。最近的新闻报道引起了人们对津巴布韦一项名为 Kariba 的特定计划的担忧，据报道该计划已产生约 1 亿美元（8000 万英镑）的收入，但存在财务尽职调查问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该公司在一份声明中表示， “决心学习津巴布韦卡里巴 REDD+ 项目的合作经验。这一承诺的核心是注重加强……整个集团的质量和风险控制以及尽职调查流程。” Heuberger 表示，他一生的荣幸是“帮助建立了一支团结一致的优秀团队，致力于提供可扩展的积极气候影响”。&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;查找更多 &lt;a href= &quot;x-gu://front/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/fronts/environment/series/the-age-of-extinction&quot;>;此处报道灭绝年龄&lt;/a>;，并关注生物多样性记者&lt;a href= “https://twitter.com/phoeb0?lang=en&quot;>;菲比·韦斯顿&lt;/a>;和&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/pgreenfielduk?lang=en&quot;>;帕特里克·格林菲尔德&lt;/a>; X&lt;/em>;&lt;em>;，以前称为 Twitter&lt;/em>;&lt;em>;，了解所有最新新闻和功能&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 20:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[The Marvels records worst ever North American opening weekend box office for MCU]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/nov/13/the-marvels-records-worst-ever-north-american-opening-weekend-performance-for-mcu-marvel-cinematic-universe]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T11:18:28Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b2e86ab89b6a5759bcb8e0f1fdaa926085623b7c/0_88_3000_1800 /master/3000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=be95bae7d73d636732570c52e05a5a0b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;《惊奇队长》中的布丽·拉尔森 (惊奇队长)。&lt;/div>;&lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/nov/08/the-marvels-review-captain-marvel-brie-larson&quot;>;漫威评论——疯狂的战斗类似泡泡糖的续集中的“量子乐队”&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;新超级英雄电影《漫威》创下了漫威电影宇宙电影有史以来北美首映周末票房最低的记录。 p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.the-numbers.com/movies/franchise/Marvel-Cinematic-Universe#tab=summary&amp;amp;franchise_movies_overview=oa3&quot;>;数据网站 Numbers 报告&lt;/a>;由布丽·拉尔森饰演惊奇队长、泰柔娜·帕里斯饰演莫妮卡·兰博、伊曼·韦拉尼饰演惊奇女士的《漫威》在美国和加拿大上映的前三天估计票房收入为 4700 万美元（3840 万英镑），这意味着它已经取代了《无敌浩克》是漫威宇宙有记录以来最差的开场；后者于 2008 年 6 月上映时管理了 5540 万美元。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;漫威的财务困难因其制作预算而变得更加复杂，据报道该预算为 2.748 亿美元，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www .the-numbers.com/movies/franchise/Marvel-Cinematic-Universe#tab=summary&amp;amp;franchise_movies_overview=od2&quot;>;所有 MCU 电影中排名第四&lt;/a>;。然而，这部电影的国际票房估计为 6300 万美元，这意味着其全球首映周末总收入为 1.103 亿美元。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/nov/02/marvel-superhero-movie-crisis-avengers&quot;>;从英雄到零：这真的是漫威的结局吗？&lt;/a>;&lt;/ p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;关于漫威表现不佳的原因，外界猜测包括演员罢工导致缺乏有效宣传、与Disney+上漫威女士系列平淡无奇的关系以及“超级英雄疲劳”导致的“超级英雄疲劳”。部分原因在于漫威及其母公司迪士尼在过去几年中决定增加电影和电视剧的产量。 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/bob-iger-disney-movie-studio-lost-focus-1235641916/#!&quot;>;迪士尼首席执行​​官鲍勃·艾格 (Bob Iger) 于 11 月 8 日表示&lt; /a>;：“我一直认为数量对于质量来说实际上可能是负面的。我认为这正是发生的事情。”他接着承认：“我们失去了一些焦点。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;自 2008 年 5 月《钢铁侠》上映以来，MCU 已经证明了迄今为止&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.the-numbers .com/movies/franchises&quot;>;好莱坞最赚钱的电影&lt;/a>;，其 33 部电影在全球影院的票房收入超过 297 亿美元（243 亿英镑）。其次最成功的是《星球大战》（103 亿美元）和《詹姆斯·邦德》（79 亿美元）。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx .net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 19:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Duterte critic Leila de Lima granted bail after six years in jail]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/13/duterte-critic-leila-de-lima-granted-bail-after-six-years-in-jail]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T10:51:05Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/340bbd135a3f0728cd292d79d70d6c0c99628430/0_70_2000_1200 /master/2000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=6ece92d65fd0fab6136ab5c6ac9d0cd9&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;前菲律宾参议员莱拉·德利马出狱&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;菲律宾前总统最著名的批评者罗德里戈·杜特尔特 (Rodrigo Duterte) 所谓的“反毒战争”在因人权组织谴责为捏造指控而入狱六年多后已获准保释。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;莱拉·德利马 (Leila de Lima)，64 岁，前参议员和周一，人权专员出庭，在支持者的欢呼声中，他们高呼“正义”和“莱拉很快就会获得自由”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在媒体和警察护送人群的簇拥下，她说：“多年来，我整个人都在呼喊正义和自由……六年多来，我一直在祈祷，祈祷这一天的到来。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;德利马于 2017 年被捕，几个月后在她对杜特尔特残酷的禁毒镇压发起参议院调查之后，这是一个&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2021/sep/15/icc-authorises-full- Inquiry-rodrigo-duterte-war-on-drugs-philippines&quot;>;国际刑事法院的调查&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;杜特尔特指责她在担任司法部长期间从贩毒团伙收受贿赂，并且她面临三项与毒品有关的指控，其中两项已被驳回。她一直否认有任何不当行为。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周一，她以健康为由寻求保释，并在最后一个悬而未决的案件中获得保释。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;联合国人权专家以及欧洲议会长期以来一直呼吁释放她，而对她作证的证人也已撤回他们的陈述。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;德利马表示，这些指控是杜特尔特的报复行为，她在案发时描述了杜特尔特的行为。被指控为“杀人犯和反社会连环杀手”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她长期以来一直批评他的治理。在担任国家人权委员会主席期间，德利马曾试图揭露达沃市所谓“敢死队”的杀戮行为，杜特尔特曾担任达沃市市长二十多年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;德利马被认为是他的政府中最著名的政治犯。在监狱里，她继续担任参议员，在拘留期间发表手写声明，经常谴责杜特尔特的治理。然而，她无法参加 2022 年的选举，并且再次竞选参议员职位的尝试失败了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周一，德利马感谢她的法律团队以及费迪南德·马科斯总统的政府Jr.，杜特尔特的继任者。她说，他的政府尊重“司法独立和法治”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;马科斯此前曾表示，他不会配合国际刑事法院对毒品战争杀戮的调查。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;根据国际刑事法院引用的数据，2016 年 7 月至 2019 年 3 月期间，估计有 12,000 至 30,000 名平民在禁毒行动中丧生。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府数据估计较低，并且据称，2016 年 7 月至 2022 年 5 月期间，至少有 6,252 人在警方行动中丧生。警方表示，任何杀戮都只是出于自卫。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 19:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Trump Jr set to return to witness stand as defense makes case in fraud trial]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/nov/13/donald-trump-jr-testify-witness-fraud-trial]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T10:00:23Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/f93922bea563c61f535280382f92d3e02ac29b8a/0_4_4899_2939 /master/4899.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=6f9e05b1723664f16c1c1ed7f6749782&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;唐纳德·特朗普本月早些时候在曼哈顿法庭外。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;小唐纳德·特朗普预计将接受家族公司的辩护律师在 2.5 亿美元的欺诈案审判中，证人第二次出庭作证。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;小特朗普是辩方证人名单中第一位出庭作证的证人，该名单还包括唐纳德·特朗普和埃里克·特朗普作为证人，但尚不清楚他们最终是否会被传唤。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www .theguardian.com/us-news/2023/nov/08/ivanka-trump-testimony-fraud-trial-what-we-learned&quot;>;伊万卡·特朗普欺诈案审判证词：我们所了解到的概览&lt;/a>; &lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;纽约总检察长办公室正在起诉特朗普、他的成年儿子以及特朗普集团的其他高管，指控他们夸大了财务报表中的资产价值。在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/nov/08/ivanka-trump-testify-fraud-trial-new-york&quot;>;伊万卡·特朗普作证&lt;/ a>;上周三。如果审判结束时特朗普被判有罪，他将面临至少 2.5 亿美元的罚款。纽约法官阿瑟·恩戈伦&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/26/trump-liable-fraud-new-york&quot;>;已经裁定&lt;/a>;特朗普应该因欺诈而吊销营业执照，尽管上诉法院正在审理该裁决。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;特朗普的长子&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023 /nov/01/donald-trump-jr-testimony-documents-fraud-trial&quot;>;于 11 月 1 日表明立场&lt;/a>;，他表示自己没有参与此案的财务报表工作——尽管他签署了多项文件文件确认其公平性和准确性 - 并表示他希望银行进行自己的“尽职调查”，而不是依赖财务报表。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我知道很多银行家都会进行自己的尽职调查，”小特朗普在证人席上说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;特朗普的团队在他第一次出庭时并未对他提出质询。他的律师将试图证明贷款人没有受到特朗普家族的伤害，并且一直在积极寻求与特朗普家族的关系。在迄今为止的证词中，特朗普家族淡化了财务报表的重要性，称这些报表完全由该组织的会计师和法律部门处理，并且家族通常手头有足够的现金来进行交易。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;不过他们收到了多份文件，显示他们就财务报表进行了咨询，并签署了用于确认家族净资产的交易，特朗普夫妇表示，他们不记得曾处理或使用过这些报表。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当特朗普本人出庭作证时，他&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/nov/06/trump-fraud-trial-speeches-grandstand&quot;>;愤怒地咆哮&lt; /a>; 针对法官兼纽约总检察长利蒂西亚·詹姆斯 (Letitia James)，他称其为“政治黑客”。他的孩子们，尤其是伊万卡·特朗普，在证人席上表现得更加平静，但同样试图削弱财务报表的重要性。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;特朗普的辩护团队表示，他们将在 12 月 15 日之前完成证人证词。审判计划持续到 12 月 22 日，但也可能在此之前结束。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 18:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Suella Braverman sacked as home secretary – UK politics live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2023/nov/13/suella-braverman-rishi-sunak-cabinet-reshuffle-conservatives-uk-politics-latest]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T08:49:20Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/079bf941c09cde5b1f350582a4da7f74ca367c08/0_1011_4024_2413 /master/4024.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=fb2ce54ff3aa764e4d09acb7057a31c0&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;内政大臣苏埃拉·布雷弗曼 (Suella Braverman) 周一离开伦敦的家。&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 16:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Rescue operation under way in India to save workers trapped after tunnel collapse]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/13/rescue-operation-under-way-in-india-to-save-workers-trapped-after-tunnel-collapse]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T08:42:22Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ff3e96b12252bf1aa0c53dacec311ec6e17bb941/0_131_2000_1200 /master/2000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=e3db0e34aeeaeb4e04278cd8adbdc988&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;救援人员在北阿坎德邦倒塌的公路隧道外&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;正在进行大规模救援行动印度北阿坎德邦的一条隧道部分倒塌，导致 40 名建筑工人被困。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Silkyara 隧道的入口于 2019 年凌晨发生倒塌，该隧道是乌塔卡希地区道路项目的一部分，正在建设中。周日早上，数十名工人在里面。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周一，官员们表示，已经使用对讲机与被困工人取得了联系，里面的所有人都还活着。通过倒塌的建筑插入漏斗，为他们提供氧气和压缩食品包。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;fa422b806ca8b34031f0937d6b70afa119998a19&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/fa422b806ca8b34031f0937d6b70afa119998a1 9 /0_229_3400_2040/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;印度北阿坎德邦 Uttarkashi 地区隧道倒塌后，救援人员聚集在现场&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;救援人员聚集在印度北阿坎德邦 Uttarkashi 区隧道塌方后的现场。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;据说工人们有大约距离隧道内的氧气耗尽还剩八到十个小时。大多数被困在里面的人都是来自全国各地的农民工。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“每个人都很安全，我们一直与被困工人保持联系，”州官员普拉桑特·库马尔 (Prashant Kumar) 说。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside >; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/mar/20/scarred-for-life-the-himalayan-towns- Sining-into-oblivion&quot;>;终生伤痕累累：喜马拉雅城镇陷入遗忘&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;在警察和国家救灾部队的监督下，救援工作进入第二阶段周一的一天，几台挖掘机和重型机械正在搬运沉重的瓦砾和碎片。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;官员们表示，20 多米的混凝土瓦砾和扭曲的金属已经被清除，但还需要 35 米才能到达北阿坎德邦首席部长普什卡·达米 (Pushkar Dhami) 周一抵达现场，并表示印度总理纳伦德拉·莫迪 (Narendra Modi) 已承诺为被困人员提供“一切可能的帮助”。 “我们希望他们很快就能获救，”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这条隧道是全长 900 公里的 Char Dam 公路项目的一部分，该项目旨在改善北阿坎德邦喜马拉雅山山区的连通性。&lt;/p>; >; &lt;p>;该项目已被证明是有争议的，并面临来自环保人士和当地人的各种法律挑战，因为它涉及在脆弱的喜马拉雅景观中钻探巨大的隧道，并与沉降、山体滑坡以及森林和当地生态侵蚀等问题有关。&lt;/ p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx .net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt; /div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 16:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia-Ukraine war live: Melitopol resistance kills Russian FSB trio – reports]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/nov/13/russia-ukraine-war-live-melitopol-resistance-kills-russian-fsb-trio-reports]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T07:51:08Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/f70e60178b4c185ae7627cb25a18aef6b07c8d50/0_216_8640_5184 /master/8640.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=d7a7b0cf6008f2f4fab0613d9b57ee9f&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;在俄罗斯战争期间，乌克兰士兵携带一架吸血鬼无人机在巴赫穆特地区执行夜间任务。实时阅读最新动态。&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 15:52:02 +0800</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Storm Debi weather warnings in place across UK and Ireland]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/13/storm-debi-weather-warnings-in-place-across-uk-and-ireland]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T06:52:15Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/28d116498a167197c38f48d19a1d46e44bf5c8b9/0_0_2992_1795 /master/2992.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=fc98d36045425fdf161611fac0f810ce&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;风暴黛比已在爱尔兰和英国发出天气警告。库存照片。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;周一，英格兰西北部部分地区发布黄色天气警报，风暴黛比袭击英国，带来大雨和强风，而爱尔兰共和国大部分地区is covered by red and orange wind warnings until mid-morning.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The alert for England is active from 10am until 4pm and has been issued for areas north of Liverpool up to Whitehaven and west to areas that include Blackpool.英国气象局警告人们应警惕强风和破坏性风，可能会导致碎片飞扬。 Damage to buildings and structures is likely and heavy items such as tiles blown from roofs may present a potential danger to life.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Met Office also warned that roads and bridges are likely to close, meaning longer journey times and public transport and other cancellations are possible, with road, rail, air and ferry services to be affected.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/oct/30/more-than-4000-english-flood-defences-almost-useless-analysis-finds&quot;>;More than 4,000 English flood defences &#39;poor or very poor&#39;, analysis finds&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;People are also warned that cuts to power, mobile phone reception, and more may occur as the storm batters power and telecommunication lines.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Those in coastal areas are warned to keep away from the waterfront, with large waves and beach material likely to be thrown on to coastal roads, sea fronts and nearby properties.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Weather warnings have been issued for large parts of the UK, as the storm is forecast to sweep across Ireland before reaching northern England and parts of Wales on Monday, with the potential for 80mph gusts in some areas.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A yellow warning for wind, the lowest level of alert, will be in place from 4am until 6pm for areas including Bangor and St Davids in Wales and Manchester, Sheffield and Liverpool in England.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Aberdeenshire in Scotland will have a yellow warning for rain from 10am until 9pm.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Parts of north-east Scotland likely to see heavy rain were also battered by Storm Babet last month, including Brechin in Angus, where hundreds of homes had to be evacuated after the river South Esk breached its banks.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Jonathan Vautrey, a meteorologist for the Met Office, urged people to “take care before you travel” as morning rush hour is expected to be affected.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“There will be some heavy rainfall, the potential for flying debris, the potential for disruption to travel and infrastructure in places,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In Ireland, an overnight red warning for east Galway and south Roscommon was extended until 7am on Monday. A yellow warning applies to every county in Ireland from midnight until 3pm on Monday.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ireland&#39;s National Emergency Co-ordination Group (NECG) advised schools and preschools in several counties to remain closed until 10am on Monday.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Jason Kelly, chief meteorologist at the Met Office, said “the strongest winds are expected to affect parts of the Republic of Ireland early on Monday, possibly coinciding with the morning commute, before affecting parts of north Wales and northern England into the afternoon.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Whilst the very strongest winds will have eased somewhat before reaching the UK, we are still expecting some significant impacts, and a wind warning has been issued.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Additionally, Debi will bring a period of heavy rain to Northern Ireland for which a combined wind and rain warning has been issued.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Simon Partridge, a spokesman for the Met Office, added “for parts of north-west Wales and England, there is a possibility of 70 to 80mph winds.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It will be a wet and blustery day for all.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 15:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Australian government will apologise to people affected by thalidomide tragedy]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/13/australian-government-thalidomide-tragedy-apology]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T06:44:13Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6ec5e985847de099069e04f8b344de11a0ab9293/272_4_5632_3380/master/5632.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f7e7a352ac69b48888ea99ba6c31c073&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Australian prime minister Anthony Albanese&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The Australian government will issue a formal apology to people affected by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/society/2012/sep/01/thalidomide-scandal-timeline&quot;>;thalidomide&lt;/a>;, the morning sickness drug that caused significant birth defects in babies during the 1950s and 1960s.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The government announced on Monday it would also unveil a national memorial site, with the prime minister, Anthony Albanese, describing the “thalidomide tragedy” as a “dark chapter” in history for Australia and the world and saying the apology was well overdue.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“In giving this apology, we will acknowledge all those babies who died and the families who mourn them, as well as those who survived but whose lives were made so much harder by the effects of this terrible drug,” Albanese said on Monday.&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/email-newsletters?CMP=copyembed&quot;>;Sign up for Guardian Australia&#39;s free morning and afternoon email newsletters for your daily news roundup&lt;/a>;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;p>;Thalidomide was marketed as a sedative and anti-nausea drug for pregnant women in the 1950s, but caused birth defects including “shortened or absent limbs, blindness, deafness or malformed internal organs”, according to Australia&#39;s Department of Health.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The drug was not tested on pregnant women before being approved, and the birth defect crisis led to greater medical oversight worldwide, including the creation of Australia&#39;s Therapeutic Goods Administration.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Worldwide, more than 10,000 children are estimated to have been born with birth defects because of thalidomide use, with an estimated 40% of these children dying within a year. Thalidomide survivors continue to live with the impacts of the drug today,” according to the TGA.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“At the time, Australia did not have a system for evaluating the safety of medicines before they were permitted on the market. Although thalidomide was ultimately removed from the market, this was only after many pregnant women in Australia had already taken the medicine.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Albanese will deliver the formal national apology to all Australians affected by the thalidomide tragedy on 29 November in Parliament House. The apology will be given “on behalf of the Australian government, parliament and the Australian people”, his office said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The following day, a national site of recognition will also be unveiled, near Canberra&#39;s Lake Burley Griffin.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Australian thalidomide survivors have welcomed the apology, which they also said was overdue.They have long called on successive federal governments to better support their health needs through more funding and services.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The government said 146 thalidomide survivors are registered with the federal Thalidomide Survivors Support Program, but it admitted the exact number of people affected by the drug is unknown.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A national apology was the first recommendation of a 2019 Senate committee report that also discussed calls from survivors for a recognition site.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The report found survivors believed Australian governments had a “moral obligation because they allowed thalidomide products to be sold in Australia without proper testing and because when Australian governments were informed about the risks of thalidomide they did not do enough to ensure that the products were removed and destroyed.”&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/sep/24/thalidomide-survivors-mourn-harold-evans-hero-friend&quot;>;Thalidomide survivors mourn Harold Evans, their hero and friend&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Despite the Department of Health being told of the dangers of thalidomide in late 1961, governments around Australia did not immediately act to destroy supplies or ban the drug&#39;s use, the report said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“When it became clear in November 1961 that thalidomide was linked to birth defects and Distillers withdrew the drug from sale, neither the state governments nor the Australian Government took swift action to ban the importation of thalidomide or to prohibit its sale. Unlike other countries, no efforts were made to recall and destroy the product that was in doctors&#39; clinics or pharmacies,” the report said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Thalidomide survivors were critical of Australian governments&#39; responses because if governments had acted more quickly they potentially could have made a significant difference,” the report said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The health minister, Mark Butler, said mothers and babies affected by thalidomide had been “let down by systemic failures”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“While we cannot change the past or end the physical suffering, I hope these important next steps of recognition and apology will help heal some of the emotional wounds,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It is difficult today to think a tragedy like thalidomide could happen, and it&#39;s a sobering reminder of our duty to put in place measures to protect people from harm.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 15:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Lib Dems seize on Braverman’s unpopularity to win over ‘blue wall’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/nov/13/lib-dems-seize-on-bravermans-unpopularity-to-win-over-blue-wall]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T06:00:25Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/0341d146bfee3943c93fc352a6250e77f50a3edf/0_15_4432_2659/master/4432.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=88f92dcd92e2adfbf004dc713dadffa0&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;The home secretary, Suella Braverman, at the Conservative Party&#39;s annual conference in Manchester, 3 October.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Suella Braverman&#39;s recent spate of controversial statements has been dismaying significant numbers of Conservative voters in “blue wall” seats, the Liberal Democrats have said, with one candidate calling her “one of our best recruiting tools”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In particular, Lib Dem campaigners said, Braverman&#39;s description of homelessness &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/nov/06/rishi-sunak-suella-braverman-lifestyle-choice-homelessness-claim&quot;>;as a “lifestyle choice”&lt;/a>; went down extremely badly with more centrist Conservative voters, many of whom raised it during doorstep chats.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;While the Lib Dems have been steadfastly refusing to say publicly how many seats they believe they could take from the Conservatives in the next election, the dismay felt by many traditional Tory supporters in the blue wall – a loose term mainly covering commuter belt areas near London – has prompted speculation it could be well above 30.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;This effect, which Lib Dem campaigners said began under Boris Johnson and Liz Truss and which Braverman has again been fuelling, could play a significant role in condemning the government to a heavy election loss – something Tory MPs in relevant seats are very aware of.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Danny Chambers, who will fight for the Conservative ultra-marginal seat of Winchester, said sentiments about Braverman were so intense that some voters whose homes were near what will be her new seat under boundary changes were delighted to learn she will not be their MP.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Chambers said a recent canvassing trip to a village on the edge of the two constituencies left him thinking Braverman was “one of our best recruiting tools”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Door after door there were people who thought they were going to have Braverman as their next MP and they were just over the moon to hear they weren&#39;t,” he said. “One guy even shouted up to his wife to come down to talk to us, for me to tell her again.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“These are proper Tory villages, and they&#39;re really pleased to see us.这主要是因为布雷弗曼。 They just find her completely distasteful.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It&#39;s weaponising homeless people or asylum seekers as part of a culture war. That&#39;s the common thread here for what people don&#39;t like – the tone, the aggression, that nastiness.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Braverman&#39;s tough line on areas such as migration did not seem to be stemming the movement of voters from the right of the Conservatives to Reform UK either, he said: “Even with some of the people that support her position on Rwanda they don&#39;t have the faith that she&#39;s going to tackle it. They&#39;re not even shoring up their vote among people who agree with them.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Lib Dem officials, who have been rigidly prioritising target seats in a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/sep/26/not-so-cuddly-lib-dems-laser-focused-on-target-list-of-seats&quot;>;highly disciplined campaign&lt;/a>;, say Braverman and Lee Anderson, the Tories&#39; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/feb/07/lee-anderson-tory-deputy-chair-one-man-controversy-machine&quot;>;combative deputy chair&lt;/a>;, are the two names which are mentioned most in blue wall seats.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Lib Dem research into swing voters in blue wall seats showed they tend to be regular donors to charities, with homelessness organisations among the most common beneficiaries, in part explaining the negative response to Braverman&#39;s comments.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Max Wilkinson, who will try to overturn the 2,500 majority of Alex Chalk, the justice secretary, in Cheltenham at the next election, said the “unpleasantness and unkindness” shown by Braverman was having an impact.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“There was one man who told me he voted leave and he had voted Conservative his whole life, but that he would now vote for whoever could get rid of them,” Wilkinson said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“He segued straight into saying how unimpressed he was by Suella Braverman, particularly on homelessness, but also about the marches.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Chalk is from the liberal edge of the Conservatives, and clearly not a fan of his colleague in the Home Office. Even this, Wilkinson said, was not necessarily in his favour.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Chalk obviously he feels very awkward about it, and I&#39;m sure he would not agree with the sort of rhetoric that&#39;s being used,” he said. “But I think people are a bit disappointed that he&#39;s not more open in condemning it.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 14:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[High silver levels in some period pants could pose health risk, study says]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/nov/13/high-silver-levels-some-period-pants-could-pose-health-risk-study]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-13T05:00:23Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/788f7a447e26cc3c81a943ec5cf5ab0e51a58e49/666_711_5861_3517/master/5861.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=327a6d2193e4eb6f4651346a9f999e7e&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Close-up of a young woman holding her hands on her belly&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Some period pants sold by high street retailers contain high levels of silver that could have health and environmental implications for consumers, an investigation has found.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Silver is used as an antimicrobial agent and is typically added to period pants to combat user concerns about smell and hygiene.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, scientists have increasingly warned about the potential health effects.美国食品和药物管理局发现纳米银可以杀死乳酸菌，这是阴道中有助于抵抗感染的健康细菌。 This can put period pant users more at risk of harmful bacteria, potentially leading to an increased risk of bacterial infections and pregnancy complications.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Natalie Hitchins, the head of home products and services at Which?, said: “Consumers should be cautious buying period pants which contain silver as experts have concerns about the health implications.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Which? believes brands should also clearly state which products contain silver so shoppers can make informed decisions about what they are buying and the possible risks.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The consumer rights group worked with an Italian consumer organisation, Altroconsumo, to independently test popular brands and check if they contained any chemicals of concern. They were worried to find that some products contained significant levels of silver, and this was not always made clear on the packaging.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Intima by Bodyform and pants by Marks &amp;amp; Spencer in particular contained notably more silver than other brands, at 126.7mg/kg and 57.8mg/kg respectively. Other brands contained 8.3mg/kg, 7.4mg/kg, and 0.9mg/kg.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Essity, the owner of Bodyform and Modibodi, said silver copper zeolite was used to “prevent odour when wearing the pants for up to 12 hours”. It added that all of its “washable underwear is certified according to Oeko-Tex Standard 100, which means that every single component has been tested for harmful substances” and “that the underwear has been designated as harmless for human health”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Marks &amp;amp; Spencer declined to comment.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Which? said it believed the use of silver was unnecessary and that previous testing by Altroconsumo had shown that textile items treated in this way did not have the promised antimicrobial properties.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The European Chemicals Agency says silver treatments, such as nanosilver and silver zeolite, are toxic to aquatic life with long-lasting effects.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The tests Which?检测结果显示，银含量超过0.1毫克/公斤，而Primark、Repeat、Wuka、Lovable和Sloggi裤子中均未发现银含量。 Sloggi&#39;s website says it does use a silver-based antimicrobial, and Primark says it uses Micro-Fresh, which contains silver chloride.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A Primark spokesperson said: “The nature of period pants means there is a potential for odour to develop during wear (in the same way that bacteria can cause socks and shoes to develop odours during wear) and our antimicrobial finish minimises such odours.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Sloggi did not reply to Which? at the time of publication.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;There are no legal limits in the UK about how much silver can be added to period pants. Manufacturers do not have to declare the presence of silver on their packaging or website.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 13 Nov 2023 13:22:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>